<ns7599:section xmlns:ns7599="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.tools.xml.xom.overview.overview">
    <ns7600:title xmlns:ns7600="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">XOM Overview</ns7600:title>
   
    <ns7601:para xmlns:ns7601="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns7602:literal xmlns:ns7602="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">XOM</ns7602:literal> (the <ns7603:emphasis xmlns:ns7603="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">XML Object Model</ns7603:emphasis>) is a tree-based
        XML processing API, similar to <ns7604:literal xmlns:ns7604="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">DOM</ns7604:literal>. The author(s) of XOM, however,
        have strived to correct many of deficiencies of DOM, as well as provide a simpler,
        more intuitive interface.
    </ns7601:para>
    <ns7605:para xmlns:ns7605="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        XOM is an open-source (LGPL) project, hosted at <ns7606:ulink xmlns:ns7606="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" url="http://www.xom.nu/"/>.
        The website also provides a lot of documentation regarding the design and rationale of
        the XOM API, as well as tutorials, unit tests, and so forth.
    </ns7605:para>
    
</ns7599:section>